# CSS Styling Guidelines

## CSS Modules Only

All component styles must use CSS Modules (`.module.css` files). Never use:
- Inline styles
- Tailwind classes
- Global CSS for components
- CSS-in-JS libraries

## CSS Custom Properties

Always use CSS variables for themeable values:

```css
.component {
  /* Text colors */
  color: var(--cc-text-primary);          /* #324D88 navy */

  /* Background colors */
  background: var(--cc-bg-paper);          /* #F5F2E8 cream */
  background: var(--cc-bg-form);           /* #A8D5D8 teal */

  /* Borders */
  border: 1px solid var(--cc-border-primary);

  /* Typography */
  font-family: var(--cc-font-typewriter);
}
```

## Color Palette

| Variable | Value | Usage |
|----------|-------|-------|
| `--cc-text-primary` | `#324D88` | Navy blue main text |
| `--cc-text-red` | `#8B1538` | Maroon accent text |
| `--cc-text-muted` | `#666666` | Muted/secondary text |
| `--cc-bg-form` | `#A8D5D8` | Light teal background |
| `--cc-bg-paper` | `#F5F2E8` | Cream paper background |
| `--cc-border-primary` | `#324D88` | Primary borders |
| `--cc-border-muted` | `#666666` | Muted borders |

## Typography

- Primary font: `var(--cc-font-typewriter)` (Berkeley Mono stack)
- Letter spacing: `0.08em` for authentic typewriter feel
- Font weights: 400 (normal), 500 (medium), 700 (bold)

## Naming Conventions

```css
/* Base component class */
.component { }

/* Variant modifiers (match prop values) */
.default { }
.dense { }
.underline { }

/* State modifiers */
.disabled { }
.focused { }
.error { }

/* Child elements */
.label { }
.input { }
.icon { }
```

## Spacing

Use the spacing scale (base: 4px):
- `4px`, `8px`, `12px`, `16px`, `20px`, `24px`, `32px`, `48px`

## Vintage Aesthetic

- Use typewriter-style fonts
- Keep borders visible and defined
- Use the established color palette
- Aim for dense, form-like layouts
- Consider print styles for form components
